192 static void MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog(void)
193 {
194  Hwi_StackInfo stackInfo;
195  Task_Stat stat;
196  bool hwiStackOverflow;
197 
198  System_printf("Data Path Stopped (last frame processing done)\n");
199 
200  /* Print DSS task statistics */
201  System_printf("DSS Task Stack Usage (Note: Task Stack Usage) ==========\n");
202 
203  Task_stat(gMmwDssMCB.initTaskHandle, &stat);
204  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d\n", "initTask",
205  stat.stackSize,
206  stat.used,
207  stat.stackSize - stat.used);
208 
209  Task_stat(gMmwDssMCB.objDetDpmTaskHandle, &stat);
210  System_printf("%20s %12s %12s %12s\n", "Task Name", "Size", "Used", "Free");
211  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d\n", "ObjDet DPM",
212  stat.stackSize,
213  stat.used,
214  stat.stackSize - stat.used);
215 
216  System_printf("HWI Stack (same as System Stack) Usage ============\n");
217  hwiStackOverflow = Hwi_getStackInfo(&stackInfo, TRUE);
218  if (hwiStackOverflow == TRUE)
219  {
220  System_printf("DSS HWI Stack overflowed\n");
221  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
222  }
223  else
224  {
225  System_printf("%20s %12s %12s %12s\n", " ", "Size", "Used", "Free");
226  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d\n", " ",
227  stackInfo.hwiStackSize,
228  stackInfo.hwiStackPeak,
229  stackInfo.hwiStackSize - stackInfo.hwiStackPeak);
230  }

253 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn
254 (
255  DPM_Report reportType,
256  uint32_t instanceId,
257  int32_t errCode,
258  uint32_t arg0,
259  uint32_t arg1
260 )
261 {
262 
263  /* Only errors are logged on the console: */
264  if (errCode != 0)
265  {
266  /* Error: Detected log on the console and die all errors are FATAL currently. */
267  System_printf ("Error: DPM Report %d received with error:%d arg0:0x%x arg1:0x%x\n",
268  reportType, errCode, arg0, arg1);
269  DebugP_assert (0);
270  }
271 
272  /* Processing further is based on the reports received: This is the control of the profile
273  * state machine: */
274  switch (reportType)
275  {
276  case DPM_Report_IOCTL:
277  {
278  /*****************************************************************
279  * DPC has been configured without an error:
280  * - This is an indication that the profile configuration commands
281  * went through without any issues.
282  *****************************************************************/
283  DebugP_log1("DSSApp: DPM Report IOCTL, command = %d\n", arg0);
284  break;
285  }
286  case DPM_Report_DPC_STARTED:
287  {
288  /*****************************************************************
289  * DPC has been started without an error:
290  * - notify sensor management task that DPC is started.
291  *****************************************************************/
292  DebugP_log0("DSSApp: DPM Report start\n");
293  break;
294  }
295  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT:
296  {
297  /*****************************************************************
298  * DPC Results have been passed:
299  * - This implies that we have valid profile results which have
300  * been received from the profile.
301  *****************************************************************/
302 
303  break;
304  }
305  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT_ACKED:
306  {
307  /*****************************************************************
308  * DPC Results have been acked:
309  * - This implies that MSS received the results.
310  *****************************************************************/
311 
312  break;
313  }
314  case DPM_Report_DPC_ASSERT:
315  {
316  DPM_DPCAssert* ptrAssert;
317 
318  /*****************************************************************
319  * DPC Fault has been detected:
320  * - This implies that the DPC has crashed.
321  * - The argument0 points to the DPC assertion information
322  *****************************************************************/
323  ptrAssert = (DPM_DPCAssert*)arg0;
324  System_printf ("DSS Exception: %s, line %d.\n", ptrAssert->fileName,
325  ptrAssert->lineNum);
326  break;
327  }
328  case DPM_Report_DPC_STOPPED:
329  {
330  /*****************************************************************
331  * DPC has been stopped without an error:
332  * - This implies that the DPC can either be reconfigured or
333  * restarted.
334  *****************************************************************/
335  DebugP_log0("DSSApp: DPM Report stop\n");
336 
337  MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog();
338  break;
339  }
340  case DPM_Report_DPC_INFO:
341  {
342  /* Currently object detection does not use this feature. */
343  break;
344  }
345  default:
346  {
347  DebugP_assert (0);
348  break;
349  }
350  }
351  return;
352 }

404  void MmwDemo_updateObjectDetStats
405 (
406  DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *currDpcStats,
407  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *outputMsgStats
408 )
409 {
410  static uint32_t prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp = 0U;
411 
412  /* Calculate interframe proc time */
413  outputMsgStats->interFrameProcessingTime =
414  (currDpcStats->interFrameEndTimeStamp - currDpcStats->interFrameStartTimeStamp)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ; /* In micro seconds */
415 
416  outputMsgStats->interChirpProcessingMargin = currDpcStats->interChirpProcessingMargin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ;
417 
418  /* Calculate interFrame processing Margin for previous frame, but saved to current frame */
419  outputMsgStats->interFrameProcessingMargin =
420  (currDpcStats->frameStartTimeStamp - prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp - currDpcStats->subFramePreparationCycles)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ;
421 
422  prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp = currDpcStats->interFrameEndTimeStamp;
423 }

438 static int32_t MmwDemo_copyResultToHSRAM
439 (
440  MmwDemo_HSRAM *ptrHsramBuffer,
441  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result,
442  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *outStats
443 )
444 {
445  uint8_t *ptrCurrBuffer;
446  uint32_t totalHsramSize;
447  uint32_t itemPayloadLen;
448 
449  /* Save result in HSRAM */
450  if(ptrHsramBuffer == NULL)
451  {
452  return -1;
453  }
454 
455  /* Save result in HSRAM */
456  if(result != NULL)
457  {
458  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult);
459  memcpy((void *)&ptrHsramBuffer->result, (void *)result, itemPayloadLen);
460  }
461  else
462  {
463  return -1;
464  }
465 
466  /* Save output Stats in HSRAM */
467  if(outStats != NULL)
468  {
469  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
470  memcpy((void *)&ptrHsramBuffer->outStats, (void *)outStats, itemPayloadLen);
471  }
472 
473  /* Set payload pointer to HSM buffer */
474  ptrCurrBuffer = &ptrHsramBuffer->payload[0];
475  totalHsramSize = MMWDEMO_HSRAM_PAYLOAD_SIZE;
476 
477  /* Save ObjOut in HSRAM */
478  if(result->objOut != NULL)
479  {
480  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut;
481  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
482  {
483  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->objOut, itemPayloadLen);
484 
485  ptrHsramBuffer->result.objOut = (DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *)ptrCurrBuffer;
486  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
487  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
488  }
489  else
490  {
491  return -1;
492  }
493  }
494 
495  /* Save ObjOutSideInfo in HSRAM */
496  if(result->objOutSideInfo != NULL)
497  {
498  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut;
499  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
500  {
501  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->objOutSideInfo, itemPayloadLen);
502  ptrHsramBuffer->result.objOutSideInfo = (DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *)ptrCurrBuffer;
503  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
504  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
505  }
506  else
507  {
508  return -1;
509  }
510  }
511 
512  /* Save DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats in HSRAM */
513  if(result->stats != NULL)
514  {
515  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats);
516  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
517  {
518  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->stats, itemPayloadLen);
519  ptrHsramBuffer->result.stats = (DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *)ptrCurrBuffer;
520  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
521  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
522  }
523  else
524  {
525  return -1;
526  }
527  }
528 
529  /* Save compRxChanBiasMeasurement in HSRAM */
530  if(result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement != NULL)
531  {
532  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg);
533  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
534  {
535  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement, itemPayloadLen);
536  ptrHsramBuffer->result.compRxChanBiasMeasurement = (DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg *)ptrCurrBuffer;
537  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
538  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
539  }
540  else
541  {
542  return -1;
543  }
544  }
545 
546  return totalHsramSize;
547 }

560 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_dpmTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
561 {
562  int32_t retVal;
563  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result;
564  volatile uint32_t startTime;
565 
566  while (1)
567  {
568  /* Execute the DPM module: */
569  retVal = DPM_execute (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, &resultBuffer);
570  if (retVal < 0) {
571  System_printf ("Error: DPM execution failed [Error code %d]\n", retVal);
572  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
573  }
574  else
575  {
576  if ((resultBuffer.size[0] == sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult)))
577  {
578  result = (DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *)resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0];
579 
580  /* Get the time stamp before copy data to HSRAM */
581  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
582 
583  /* Update processing stats and added it to buffer 1*/
584  MmwDemo_updateObjectDetStats(result->stats,
585  &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.subFrameStats[result->subFrameIdx]);
586 
587  /* Copy result data to HSRAM */
588  if ((retVal = MmwDemo_copyResultToHSRAM(&gHSRAM, result, &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.subFrameStats[result->subFrameIdx])) >= 0)
589  {
590  /* Update interframe margin with HSRAM copy time */
591  gHSRAM.outStats.interFrameProcessingMargin -= ((Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
592 
593  /* Update DPM buffer */
594  resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0] = (uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.result;
595  resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[1] = (uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.outStats;
596  resultBuffer.size[1] = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
597 
598  /* YES: Results are available send them. */
599  retVal = DPM_sendResult (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, true, &resultBuffer);
600  if (retVal < 0)
601  {
602  System_printf ("Error: Failed to send results [Error: %d] to remote\n", retVal);
603  }
604  }
605  else
606  {
607  System_printf ("Error: Failed to copy processing results to HSRAM, error=%d\n", retVal);
608  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
609  }
610  }
611  }
612  }
613 }

624 static void MmwDemo_dssInitTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
625 {
626  int32_t errCode;
627  Task_Params taskParams;
628  DPM_InitCfg dpmInitCfg;
629  DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams objDetInitParams;
630  uint32_t edmaCCIdx;
631 
632  /*****************************************************************************
633  * Driver Init:
634  *****************************************************************************/
635 
636  /* Initialize the Mailbox */
637  Mailbox_init(MAILBOX_TYPE_DSS);
638 
639  /*****************************************************************************
640  * Driver Open/Configuraiton:
641  *****************************************************************************/
642 
643  /* Initialize the Data Path: */
644  MmwDemo_dataPathInit(&gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj);
645  MmwDemo_dataPathOpen(&gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj);
646 
647  /*****************************************************************************
648  * Initialization of the DPM Module:
649  *****************************************************************************/
650  memset ((void *)&objDetInitParams, 0, sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams));
651 
652  objDetInitParams.L3ramCfg.addr = (void *)&gMmwL3[0];
653  objDetInitParams.L3ramCfg.size = sizeof(gMmwL3);
654  objDetInitParams.CoreL2RamCfg.addr = &gDPC_ObjDetL2Heap[0];
655  objDetInitParams.CoreL2RamCfg.size = sizeof(gDPC_ObjDetL2Heap);
656  objDetInitParams.CoreL1RamCfg.addr = &gDPC_ObjDetL1Heap[0];
657  objDetInitParams.CoreL1RamCfg.size = sizeof(gDPC_ObjDetL1Heap);
658  for (edmaCCIdx = 0; edmaCCIdx < EDMA_NUM_CC; edmaCCIdx++)
659  {
660  objDetInitParams.edmaHandle[edmaCCIdx] = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.edmaHandle[edmaCCIdx];
661  }
662 
663  /* DPC Call-back config */
664  objDetInitParams.processCallBackCfg.processFrameBeginCallBackFxn =
665  MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_processFrameBeginCallBackFxn;
666  objDetInitParams.processCallBackCfg.processInterFrameBeginCallBackFxn =
667  MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_processInterFrameBeginCallBackFxn;
668 
669  memset ((void *)&dpmInitCfg, 0, sizeof(DPM_InitCfg));
670 
671  /* Setup the configuration: */
672  dpmInitCfg.socHandle = gMmwDssMCB.socHandle;
673  dpmInitCfg.ptrProcChainCfg = &gDPC_ObjectDetectionCfg;
674  dpmInitCfg.instanceId = 0xFEEDFEED;
675  dpmInitCfg.domain = DPM_Domain_REMOTE;
676  dpmInitCfg.reportFxn = MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn;
677  dpmInitCfg.arg = &objDetInitParams;
678  dpmInitCfg.argSize = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams);
679 
680  /* Initialize the DPM Module: */
681  gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle = DPM_init (&dpmInitCfg, &errCode);
682  if (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle == NULL)
683  {
684  System_printf ("Error: Unable to initialize the DPM Module [Error: %d]\n", errCode);
685  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
686  return;
687  }
688 
689  /* Synchronization: This will synchronize the execution of the control module
690  * between the domains. This is a prerequiste and always needs to be invoked. */
691  while (1)
692  {
693  int32_t syncStatus;
694 
695  /* Get the synchronization status: */
696  syncStatus = DPM_synch (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, &errCode);
697  if (syncStatus < 0)
698  {
699  /* Error: Unable to synchronize the framework */
700  System_printf ("Error: DPM Synchronization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
701  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
702  return;
703  }
704  if (syncStatus == 1)
705  {
706  /* Synchronization acheived: */
707  break;
708  }
709  /* Sleep and poll again: */
710  Task_sleep(1);
711  }
712  System_printf ("Debug: DPM Module Sync is done\n");
713 
714  /* Launch the DPM Task */
715  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
716  taskParams.priority = MMWDEMO_DPC_OBJDET_DPM_TASK_PRIORITY;
717  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
718  gMmwDssMCB.objDetDpmTaskHandle = Task_create(MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_dpmTask, &taskParams, NULL);
719 
720  return;
721 }

747 int main (void)
748 {
749  Task_Params taskParams;
750  int32_t errCode;
751  SOC_Handle socHandle;
752  SOC_Cfg socCfg;
753 
754  /* Initialize and populate the demo MCB */
755  memset ((void*)&gMmwDssMCB, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_DSS_MCB));
756 
757  /* Initialize the SOC confiugration: */
758  memset ((void *)&socCfg, 0, sizeof(SOC_Cfg));
759 
760  /* Populate the SOC configuration: */
761  socCfg.clockCfg = SOC_SysClock_BYPASS_INIT;
762 
763  /* Initialize the SOC Module: This is done as soon as the application is started
764  * to ensure that the MPU is correctly configured. */
765  socHandle = SOC_init (&socCfg, &errCode);
766  if (socHandle == NULL)
767  {
768  System_printf ("Error: SOC Module Initialization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
769  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
770  return -1;
771  }
772 
773  gMmwDssMCB.socHandle = socHandle;
774 
775  /* Initialize the Task Parameters. */
776  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
777  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
778  gMmwDssMCB.initTaskHandle = Task_create(MmwDemo_dssInitTask, &taskParams, NULL);
779 
780  /* Start BIOS */
781  BIOS_start();
782  return 0;
